    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6">
        <p class="HeaderA-Level2">What Is An Information <br>Security Event?</p>
        <p>A security event is an observable change in the normal operation of a network, IT service, website or application that identifies when a security policy or safeguard has failed. Security events are usually tied to systems, applications or data that play a significant role in the overall security of the system.</p>
        <p>cWatch Web’s Security & Event Management (SIEM) sofware is used to identify these events for you and offer the ability to manage them by providing real-time analysis, alerts and context so humans can quickly investigate before it becomes a security incident.</p>
      </div>
